      "content": "yeah but if renewables can't do the heavy lifting on their own for a stable grid, isn't it kind of a false equivalence to treat the \"nuclear vs renewables\" debate as if they're equally valid options? like, if the physics says we need baseload power that wind/solar can't provide 24/7, isn't nuclear basically the only realistic path forward?",
